{"id":"9763","name":"Save Show Notes","tagline":"Get podcast show notes and save them for later.","icon":"ios15 c4271458815 g59853","latest":"32794","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>This shortcut is designed to take show notes from the currently playing podcast in Overcast and save them to a note in Drafts, and as a to-do item in Things for future review.</p>\n<p>It could be adapted to save them in other notes and task management apps.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>The origin of this shortcut is documented <a href=\"https://heydingus.net/blog/2021/7/shortcuts-tips-saving-podcast-show-notes-for-later\">on HeyDingus.net</a>.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.2 - April 19, 2022, 11:47 p.m.</strong></p><p>- Removed the 'If' action that routed to separate Things actions depending on the platform, since now the same actions work across platforms.<br>- Added addition explanation comments in preparation for submission to MacStories' #AutomationApril contest.</p>"}